---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import PhotoSlideshow from '../components/PhotoSlideshow.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | ANTLATT.COM" description="About Anthony Lattanzio - tech enthusiast, builder, and homelab operator.">
  <Hero title="About Me" />

  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <!-- Photo Gallery Section -->
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-8 lg:gap-12 items-start">
      <!-- Slideshow Column -->
      <div class="w-full lg:w-2/5 flex-shrink-0">
        <PhotoSlideshow />
      </div>
      
      <!-- Content Column -->
      <div class="flex-1 prose prose-lg">
        <h2>Hey, I'm Anthony.</h2>
      
      <p>
        I'm a tech enthusiast who likes to build things. If it involves hardware, software, 
        or ideally both, I'm probably interested. This site is where I document my projects — 
        some practical, some ridiculous, all fun.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Do</h2>
      
      <p>
        By day, I work in tech. By night, I run a homelab that's grown way beyond what 
        any reasonable person needs in their house. Current infrastructure includes:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Qdrant</strong> — Vector database for AI memory systems</li>
        <li><strong>Redis</strong> — Fast buffer for real-time data</li>
        <li><strong>Ollama</strong> — Local LLM inference (qwen3, mxbai-embed-large)</li>
        <li><strong>True-Recall</strong> — A JARVIS-like persistent memory system for AI assistants</li>
        <li><strong>Various other services</strong> — More containers than I'd like to admit</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Philosophy</h2>
      
      <p>
        I believe in learning by building. Every project on this site started with 
        "I wonder if I could..." and ended with either a working solution or a 
        spectacular failure. Both are valuable.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        I also believe in self-hosting when it makes sense. There's something satisfying 
        about running your own infrastructure — knowing exactly where your data lives 
        and having complete control over your tools.
      </p>

      <h2>This Site</h2>
      
      <p>
        Built with <strong>Astro</strong>, styled with <strong>Tailwind CSS</strong>, 
        self-hosted on <strong>Docker with nginx</strong>. Fast, simple, no tracking, no nonsense.
      </p>

      <p>
        The site runs in a Docker container on my homelab, served via nginx. 
        This gives me full control over hosting and makes it easy to integrate with 
        my other self-hosted services like the AI-powered search.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        Check out the <a href="/lab">Lab Status</a> page to see the live status of 
        all my infrastructure.
      </p>

      <h2>Experiments & Side Projects</h2>
      
      <p>
        Not everything fits neatly into "homelab" or "builds." Sometimes I go down rabbit holes 
        that lead to <a href="/deepfakes">AI-powered deepfake experiments</a> — face swaps, 
        movie recasts, and learning how neural networks process faces. It's the same spirit of 
        curiosity, just with more GPU hours.
      </p>

      <h2>Get In Touch</h2>
      
      <p>
        Questions about a project? Want to collaborate? Just want to say hi?
        Head over to the <a href="/contact">contact page</a> or find me on the links below.
      </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>